---
title: Facebook Plans to Merge Messenger, Instagram and Whatsapp Infrastructure

date: 2019-01-25 #this is the publication date, and controls display order.

# description: meta description for post.

category: brief

---

The instant messaging platforms Facebook Messenger, WhatsApp, and Instagram [will soon utilize the same technical infrastructure.][/link] This announcement came from Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg, whose company has owned both Instagram and WhatsApp since 2014. While the three services will continue to function as standalone applications, this decision has sparked concern that this is another step by Facebook toward monopolizing the social media market. The decision also raises questions surrounding the privacy of users, as data from one platform could be potentially shared within all three. [The German government moved to block the measures for its citizens][/link2] without “voluntary consent,” a move Facebook promised to appeal.

[link]: https://www.nytimes.com/2019/01/25/technology/facebook-instagram-whatsapp-messenger.html
[link2]: https://thenextweb.com/facebook/2019/02/08/why-germany-wants-to-block-facebooks-messenger-instagram-whatsapp-merger/
